    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-28T05:31:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-28T05:31:00-05:00" n="664"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d664">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Lot 55D128: Black Book, Tab 41: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief, Far East</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ridgway</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Joint Chiefs of
                            Staff</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-28T19:31:00+09:00">28
                            October 1951—7:31 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>CX–56073. Acknowledge your msg nr 85254.<note n="1" xml:id="d664fn1">See footnote
                        1 to telegram C–55922, <ref target="#pg_1066">p. 1066</ref>.</note> When
                    Bradley and Bohlen were here, all were in agreement that when map with our <pb
                        facs="1088" n="1072" xml:id="pg_1072"/> proposed demilitarized zone was
                    given to Communists, it would be, with only minor changes, our final offer.
                    Understood this had your full approval. Accordingly, I plan little change in our
                    proposed zone except to reflect further 8th Army advances. Request
                    confirmation.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
